template_id: openagreements-restrictive-covenant-alaska
name: OpenAgreements Employee Restrictive Covenant (Alaska)
category: non-compete
description: >-
  Alaska-specific employee restrictive covenant agreement built for Alaska's
  pure common-law reasonableness regime: there is no general Alaska non-compete
  statute, so every post-employment restraint stands or falls on Alaska Supreme
  Court case law — non-competition agreements are strictly construed
  (DeCristofaro v. Sec. Nat'l Bank) and weighed against the Data Management,
  Inc. v. Greene reasonableness factors (reasonably necessary to protect a
  legitimate business interest and no broader than needed). It provides
  confidentiality and trade-secret protection backstopped by the Alaska Uniform
  Trade Secrets Act (AS 45.50.910–.945), customer and employee
  non-solicitation, an optional customer non-dealing covenant scoped to the
  customers and information the employer procured at its own expense (Metcalfe
  Invs., Inc. v. Garrison), an optional non-compete drawn to the reasonable-
  necessity gate, optional non-investment, sale-of-business public-injury
  weighing for covenants tied to a business sale (Dominic Wenzell, DMD PC v.
  Ingrim), and a reasonable-alteration posture that the drafting does not rely
  on — Data Management makes judicial rescue of an overbroad covenant available
  only to an employer that carries the burden of proving good-faith drafting,
  with willful overreach forfeiting alteration. Drafted as a starting point for
  licensed counsel review.
